                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-signs, indicating the place where the omitted passage, written in the upper margin belong: fols. 2rb, 61rb, 63ra, 64vb, 66rb, 69va.&#xD;
- Omitted letters and words written interlineally: e.g., fols. 68rb, 71vab, 73ra.&#xD;
- Rubrication not executed on fols. 70v-73v (hand b).&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names of the donor(s) are left unfilled (hand b): fols. e.g., fols. 66va, 67vb, 68rb.&#xD;
- Illegible note in pencil on fol. 75v.&#xD;
- Fols. 76 and 77 (quire B) are a fragment of an older Ms. inserted in the codex sideways; they contain ʿarke-hymns addressing different saints.</item>
